In [62]:
cols_with_zeros = ['Glucose', 'BloodPressure', 'SkinThickness', \
                   'BMI', 'Insulin']


# replace the zeros in the above columns with mean
for column in cols_with_zeros:
    X_train[column] = X_train[column].replace(0, np.NaN)
    mean = int(X_train[column].mean(skipna=True))
    X_train[column] = X_train[column].replace(np.NaN, mean)

In [69]:
# Determine the false positive and true positive rates
FPR1, TPR1, _ = roc_curve(y_train, y_pred_train1)
FPR2, TPR2, _ = roc_curve(y_test, y_pred_test1)
FPR3, TPR3, _ = roc_curve(y_test, y_pred_test2)

# Calculate the AUC

roc_auc1 = auc(FPR1, TPR1)
print ('ROC AUC: %0.3f' % roc_auc1 )

roc_auc2 = auc(FPR2, TPR2)
print ('ROC AUC: %0.3f' % roc_auc2 )

roc_auc3 = auc(FPR3, TPR3)
print ('ROC AUC: %0.3f' % roc_auc3 )

ROC AUC: 0.719
ROC AUC: 0.717
ROC AUC: 0.721
In [70]:
# Plot of a ROC curve
plt.figure(figsize=(10,10))
plt.plot(FPR1, TPR1, label='ROC curve1 (area = %0.3f)' % roc_auc1)
plt.plot(FPR2, TPR2, label='ROC curve2 (area = %0.3f)' % roc_auc2)
plt.plot(FPR3, TPR3, label='ROC curve3 (area = %0.3f)' % roc_auc3)
plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], 'k--')
plt.xlim([-0.05, 1.0])
plt.ylim([0.0, 1.05])
plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate')
plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate')
plt.title('ROC Curve')
plt.legend(loc="lower right")
plt.show();
